I'm glad the corrected code is working as intended. Here's an example of how to add unit tests using the `@test` and `@testset` macros.

```julia
using Test

abstract type AbstractVehicle end

struct Car <: AbstractVehicle end
struct Motorcycle <: AbstractVehicle end
struct Bus <: AbstractVehicle end
struct Truck <: AbstractVehicle end

function ispersonal(vehicle::AbstractVehicle)
    isa(vehicle, Car) || isa(vehicle, Motorcycle)
end

@testset "personal vehicle tests" begin
    @test ispersonal(Car()) == true
    @test ispersonal(Motorcycle()) == true
    @test ispersonal(Bus()) == false
    @test ispersonal(Truck()) == false
end
```

This test suite checks the correct behavior of the `ispersonal` function for each of the given vehicle types.

